This repository generates 'A Makefile for Developing Containerized LaTeX Technical Documents Template':
- https://arxiv.org/abs/2005.12660

Requirements:
- Docker https://docs.docker.com/get-docker/
- Make https://www.gnu.org/software/make/
- [Optional] NVIDIA Container Toolkit https://docs.nvidia.com/datacenter/cloud-native/container-toolkit/install-guide.html

Preparation:
1. git clone https://github.com/pbizopoulos/a-makefile-for-developing-containerized-latex-technical-documents-template
2. cd a-makefile-for-developing-containerized-latex-technical-documents-template/
3. sudo systemctl start docker

Usage:
make				# Generate draft (fast) version document.
make VERSION=--full 		# Generate full (slow) version document.
make clean 			# Remove tmp/ directory.
make tmp/format-python 		# Format main.py using autopep8 and isort.
make tmp/lint-texlive 		# Lint ms.tex using chktex and lacheck.
make tmp/arxiv.tar 		# Generate a tar file for uploading to arxiv.
make tmp/download-arxiv 	# Download tar from arxiv.
make tmp/update-makefile	# Update Makefile.
make tmp/update-docker-images 	# Update docker images.
